 Shuturmurgh

 Written by Gayandev Agnihotri, the Hindi play uses the figure of the ostrich (shuturmurgh) as a metaphor to denote society?s wilful ignorance of and total detachment from present-day politics. The Little Thespian production is directed by S.M. Azhar Alam. 

 Catch it at Tapan Theatre, 6.30 pm, on July 19

